<subSubSection pageId="156" pageNumber="157" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="156.[264,1323,367,713]" pageId="156" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,432,446,472]" pageId="156" pageNumber="157">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Head compressed anteriorly or spherical; eyes separated by a distance usually larger than ocellus; fronto­orbital plate with 1­3 rows of hairs laterally, never swollen; dorsal facets of eyes larger than ventral facets; inner margins of eyes parallel. Parafacial bare; lower margin of face perpendicular or projecting; Sublunular bulla indistinct. First flagellomere short; oral opening short. Thorax black, scale­like setae absent. Scutellum with two pairs of marginal setae. Abdomen subovate, black or with yellow spots. Female sternite VII variable in shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
